"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.18.1.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.18.1.2</span> 標題：陶罐（clay jar）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כַּד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kad)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:14\">GEN 24:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:15\">GEN 24:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:16\">GEN 24:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:17\">GEN 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:18\">GEN 24:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:20\">GEN 24:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:43\">GEN 24:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:45\">GEN 24:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:46\">GEN 24:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:16\">JDG 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:16\">JDG 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:19\">JDG 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:20\">JDG 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:12\">1KI 17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:14\">1KI 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:34\">1KI 18:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:6\">ECC 12:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： נֵבֶל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： nevel)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:14\">ISA 30:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:2\">LAM 4:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： צַפַּחַת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： tsapachath)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:12\">1SA 26:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:16\">1SA 26:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:12\">1KI 17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:14\">1KI 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:6\">1KI 19:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： κεράμιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： keramion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:13\">MRK 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:10\">LUK 22:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ὑδρία</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： hudria)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28\">JHN 4:28</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0059_women_drawing_water_into_jars.png\" alt=\"OAI-0059_women_drawing_water_into_jars\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\"> (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>陶罐是一種陶製器皿，用來儲存葡萄酒和橄欖油等液體（另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">5.18.1 儲存容器 (containers for storage)&lt;REALIA:5.18.1&gt;</a> ）。陶罐也可以用來裝水或其他液體。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>石缸（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">5.18.1.1 石缸 (stone jar)&lt;REALIA:5.18.1.1&gt;</a> ）只是用來儲水。陶罐與石缸不同，裝滿水後必須要足夠輕，以便婦女能夠拿著走路；在當時的社會，打水工作通常由婦女來做。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:6\">JHN 2:6</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28\">JHN 4:28</a> 中，約翰使用了同一個意為「罐」的希臘文詞語（《和修》2:6譯作「缸」，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28\">JHN 4:28</a> 「水罐」），但從上下文可以清楚地看出，這個詞指的是兩種不同的容器。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28\">JHN 4:28</a> 提到的婦女不可能提著一口沉重的石缸。大多數譯本都譯為「水罐」（“water jar”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。目標語言如果使用不同的詞語來分別表示打水或提水的器皿與喝水的器皿，就應使用表示前者的詞語。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
